im phill bass raver owen . i have a 2 hour show on www.renegaderadio.co.uk & 107.2 fm  4-6 gmt ever friday . i play breaks , 90s happy hardcore , jungle ,dnb and oldskool 

Originally from Leicester now living in Durham with my wife and 2 dogs. I first got into listening to Old Skool when I was about 13, trading tapes at school. The first tape I got was Top Buzz Fantazia New Years Eve ‘91 and after that I was hooked. I spent the next couple of years collecting tapes from ‘92 raves (Dreamscape, Fantazia etc). I went to my first rave at 14, which was a Total Kaos event in Leicester and continued going to raves for the next 4 years spending most weekends in Die Hard in Leicester where my love of Happy Hardcore developed.
At the age of 15 I bought my first pair of decks, belt drives Soundlabs and started buying vinyl. If I heard something I liked in a club then I would do what I could to find out what the track was so I could add it to my collection. I bought mainly happy hardcore and techno with a few drum and bass and jungle thrown in.
After nearly 3 years of belt drives I brought a pair of 1210s and was all set to try and take my djing to another level but sadly due to a lack of time, money and my health I had to sell them and total gave it up. However I kept all my vinyl (apart from a few I sold on eBay) hoping one day to be able to restart djing and thankfully 15 years later this has happened.
Fast forward to 2011 I bought a cheap pair of decks to try and reignite the spark, within days I was hooked again. I then found www.its-all-about-oldskool.com and enjoyed chatting with everyone about the old days. This is where I met Puffa, Livvy and alot of the renegade crew. After buying a pair of new direct drives and serato I began posting a few mixes online. Then Puffa and livvy  gave me the opportunity to play on Renegade. 

always Looking for  new tracks for my show on www.renegaderadio.co.uk . Any promos would be gratefully appreciated, thanks Bassraver :-)

Take a walk on the wild side with the next big thing from France... Putting together many influences, DWAIL works hard in order to create a unique mixture and their own personal sound. With heavy, fast, "rock'n'roll" and dissonant tones, or groovy and deconstructed structures, the band plays within a wide range of sounds, which allows their music to evolve from song to song and offers a varied and punchy Rock'n'rollcore. An otherworldly electric energy radiates from their lead screamer Yannock and the extremly talented (21 year old) girl Léa on the drums!

"Monstro" their first EP, released in 2006 introduced the band to the local metal scene. They performed in every part of France, in Luxembourg and in Switzerland, in venues such as La Locomotive in Paris or Le Bikini in Toulouse, opening for bands such as Gojira, Amon Amarth, Septic Flesh and many more...

Their first album "HELTER SKELTER" was released in 2011 on the label Klonosphere / Season Of Mist. This time, the band called on LOGAN MADER (Gojira, Soulfly, Cavalera Conspiracy...) for the mix and the mastering of the album. With this record the band performed more than 40 shows in France ( chosen for the Hellfest Battle ) and confirmed their potential as a crushing live band!

“The Human Concern Part One", first chapter of their new album named “The Human Concern", will be released on 3 June 2013, once again by Klonosphere / SOM. It will be followed by a tour starting in Septembre 2013!

The idea behind this album was to deal with ufology. It tells the same story but from two different angles. “The Human Concern Part One", which is the first part of this project, will tell the story of what looks like to be an attack, from a human point of view... The organic, abrasive and explosive sound of this first chapter makes it a unique experience.

Visit TradingGator for an easy, step-by-step guide to rolling over your 401(k) to a gold IRA.

A rollover 401k to a gold IRA can be quite a lot easier than you might think. The 401k, like the pension, is a kind of annuity that protects your investment in the employer's company and offers the tax-deferred benefits of an IRA. But the main difference between a 401k and an IRA is that the IRA is taxed while the 401k is not.

The 401k is a fantastic way to save money as well as make investments while having those profits taxed at the individual level rather than the corporate level. That is one reason why so many people want to rollover their 401k to a gold IRA. If you're looking for the best way to do this, we have some advice.

Here's the scoop on rolling over your 401k to a gold IRA. It is fairly simple and takes only a couple of minutes to complete. In fact, you can complete the entire process in under 15 minutes with the help of a broker or financial advisor.

There are two basic approaches to handling the rollover. First is to use an online IRA provider to handle the transaction for you. For example, there are some providers out there that charge a fee to complete the entire rollover, but you get the benefit of convenience. And there are those that charge no fee and use an online system to process the transaction.

The second approach is to hire a broker or financial advisor to handle the transaction for you. This means the deal will cost more, since you will need to pay a broker to handle the conversion, but it can be a great way to save time and money.

Rolling over your 401k is fairly simple. We highly recommend hiring a broker or financial advisor to handle the entire process. The advantages to this approach are that the conversion is completed quickly and smoothly and you will save money on fees, especially if you use an online IRA provider.

Here's how it works: When you have more money saved up to use for a golden age and retirement, you rollover your 401k to a gold IRA. When you're retired, you convert your 401k to a regular IRA, thus earning the interest and tax-deferred benefits that come with such an account.

There is a certain amount of penalty and tax involved when you transfer your 401k to a traditional IRA. But there is no penalty or tax when you rollover your 401k to a gold IRA. It is considered a non-taxable transaction.

You will want to go through the traditional IRA trustee to figure out what you can do with your savings. Of course, these days many people have 401k's held in a high-yield or ultra-low-risk account.

There are three ways to rollover your 401k to a gold IRA. You can convert it right now, which will save you some money, or you can wait a year or two before converting it, or you can use a broker or financial advisor to do the conversion for you. With either route, the result is the same: saving money by converting your 401k to a gold IRA.

Since a gold IRA is not taxed, you have an additional asset that will be taxed. The advantage to this is that you will not pay taxes on your gold IRA income while you are still working. The lower your taxes will be, the more money you can contribute to your golden and retirement plan.

If you are planning to move your 401k to a traditional retirement accounts, you should know that such a move will not affect your taxes, but the conversion to a gold IRA may change them. Some may even consider that a benefit.

THE MAN- In the era of the Rapper slash actor, slash business mogul, slash pro sports team co-owner and anything in between, being a man of many hats has become not only fashionable…but it is also a certified standard.  Welcome to 2018, Where we find a 30 something year old Hip-Hop Culture, sitting (with one leg crossed) in a plush cigar lounge in Harlem NYC, sipping fine wine, and puffing hand rolled cigars with a 40 something year old, vino obsessed gentleman by the name of Cab Cabernet. Now, the fact that a rapper owns a cigar lounge, is not surprising at all these days. The head scratcher is that he became a self-made lifestyle connoisseur outside of the music industry. Which makes him one of a spoonful of Rappers who can claim they do it for fun, and actually mean it. And although Mr. Cabernet was not raised with a silver spoon in his mouth, his has been a life of many rich adventures. In his own words: “I have lived many lives, and Krushed Grapes embodies all of them”. 

THE BRAND- So what is Krushed Grapes? Well, aside from being another term for wine, “KG LIFESTYLE” (Krushed Grapes Lifestyle) is the brand name of a sophisticated lifestyle products/services company owned by Mr. Cabernet which includes wine, music, cigars, footwear, accessories, lingerie, tours, TV, film, events, and much more. Krushed Grapes is a lifestyle. The lifestyle of enjoying life to the fullest.
THE MUSIC-“KRUSHED GRAPES: HARLEM VINTAGE is like a soundtrack to the lifestyle. When you press PLAY, you will experience a day in the life of the artist, the entrepreneur, the oenophile, the adventurer, the playboy, the lifestyle connoisseur, in the setting of Renaissance Harlem.  Stand outs include the descriptive “Le’ Connoisseur”,  the self-explanatory “Mr. Cabernet”, “Chardonnay” which highlights Cab’s admiration of wine & women, the feel good anthem "Good Times", and “The Ritz” the koolest  Hip-Hop cover out of the many versions of Irving Berlin’s timeless classic recording. Unlike the 1st KG project aptly titled “Krushed Grapes” (2008), which focused strictly on the sexual aspect of the lifestyle, the new album is more of a celebration of the lifestyle in totality. The music, The lost era, fashion, art, leisure, as well as pleasure. . Cab’s lyricism is the refined class of a vintage wine, paired with the style & soul of old Harlem, and the rich, full flavor of a hand rolled cigar. This is grown man Lifestyle music, for those who appreciate the finer things in life. Mr. Cabernet could quite possibly be the most sophisticated Rapper alive. A student of high culture. A distinguished gentleman. A man of many hats… figuratively and literally. He actually owns over 200.

THE ADVENTURE- Back in 1994 while living in his hometown of New England, he and his local Rap group were discovered by a Major record label during his senior year of High School. Within just 2 months he was signed to the label and immediately relocated to NYC and began ghost writing for Gold and Platinum R&B recording artists. In 2001, he co-founded the Bukarance Records imprint which released music for the next 5 years with various distributors worldwide. In winter of 2006, after a 13 year roller coaster career in the music biz, Cab took a break from that lifestyle, and created a new one. The former underground Hip-Hop artist (Hanif-Jamiyl of Maspyke) transformed into the founder of a private all male escort service for the pleasure of women only. Not only did this service pay the bills (and offer many other interesting perks), but more importantly, it led to the birth of the Krushed Grapes Lifestyle and Empire to be. “KRUSHED GRAPES: HARLEM VINTAGE” is a documentation as well as a celebration of this extraordinary lifestyle. Part James Bond, part  Ralph Lauren, part Billy D, and 2 cubes of ice, Mr. Cabernet is the epitome of class, and refinement with a debonair flair…and a bop from way back when.  In the charismatic words of Mr. Cabernet, “Krushed Grapes Is A Lifestyle…Sip It Slow”.
